en_182664_0	The employees of the National Water Supply and Drainage Board they on a four-hour strike today (Feb. 02) demanding to resolve their salary issues.
en_182664_1	The convener of the Joint Water Supply Trade Union Alliance, engineer Upali Ratnayake said they decided to take this initiative as the authorities are not responding to their demands.
en_182664_2	Meanwhile issuing a communiqué, the National Water Supply and Drainage Board said that the management had held a discussion with trade unions to make a fair salary increase.
en_182664_3	The communiqué said that it was decided at the meeting to hold discussions with Minister Rauff Hakeem to find a solution.
